article.headline: UTEP 73, UCF 68
article.story: EL PASO, Texas -- Randy Culpepper's 25 points helped lead Texas-El Paso to a 73-68 victory over Central Florida on Wednesday night. Culpepper was 14-of-16 in shooting from the free throw line and 3-of-8 in shooting from 3-point range for the Miners (14-9, 5-4 Conference USA). Tavaris Watts added 11 points off the bench, while Stefon Jackson was the only UTEP starter to reach double digits with 22 points. The Miners overcame a strong shooting night from Central Florida's Jermaine Taylor. Taylor scored 38 points for UCF (15-9, 5-5) and made 13-of-22 field goals. Tony Davis scored nine points and pulled down 12 rebounds in the loss. Central Florida led 33-31 at the half.
